	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				This guy cons yellow to me at 19 and is easy to take out if you know what you are doing. He is a ranger which isnt hard to figure out seeing how he has kicking abilities, casts some druid spells, and Carries a fine steel short sword most of the time which can be carried by a limited amount of classes and only 3 of those classes are casters. He hits me for 14points of damage normally. He occasionally gets up to around 30 points and it is very rare that he hits for 40 unless your defense sucks. He is best taken on with a partner if you are trying to take him out at around 18 or 19 because he can get the best of you. He is very good exp though and there are no faction hits. He gives you a warning but that is it. It is best if you take him out by peaking in the crack in the door and then Casting a DoT spell then proceeding to nuke like there was no tomorrow, but if you are a non caster then your only choice(which is a bad one considering he can get a good amount of hits off you this way) is to go to the back of the house by the chimney and say I will kill you. Well thats my 2cp.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
